===from:Allan
===date:Thu Oct 24 21:50:22 2002
===subject:Tradition-a question
===message:Great discussion.

I'll play devils advocate.  What if it was the last whale and by some strange coincidence they were still legally allowed to kill the whale?

I was asked this in a conservation class as an undergrad because this question actually arises all the time in the real world. REALLY IT DOES.

I would have to say let them kill it because I believe so strongly in rights being honored.  But I really could not blame people from stopping it or acting illegally if they felt so inclined.  If I were put to the test I would probrably do what I "felt" was right.  Then again I honestly think extinction is a natural process and I am often not in favor of spending gobs of money to save, or try to save small numbers of a species that really has not true future on the planet without help.  Even if we were the cause.

Remember too that many times it is the cute animals (Koala, Panda etc.) that get all the attention when often times it is slimy disgusting worms and bugs that go extinct because they are not the "in thing to save". 

This should get a response.

Allan
=========yorg=========
